The Projects tab is the main landing page of the Video Designer application and provides an overview of all created Projects. It consists of two main areas:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- **Project top toolbar** with **search field** and **New Project** action button

- **Project list area **containing all existing Projects

The table in the Projects tab contains the following columns:

Field

Description

**Thumbnail**

Thumbnail image of the Pvideo Project

**Title**

Name of the Project

**Date modified**

Date and time when the Project was last modified

> Tip: Sort and search

The Projects table can be searched and sorted to easily find a particular Project. Use the full-text search field to search by title or by date.

Click on a column header to sort that column in ascending or descending order. Click again to change the sorting or return to the default sorting.

## User actions on Projects
The following actions can be performed from the Projects tab:

- **Create a new Project** by clicking the **New Project** button

- **Open an existing Project** by clicking its **thumbnail **or the **Edit** button (appears on mouseover)

- **Go to the settings** of an existing Project by clicking the **three-dot menu** (appears on mouseover) &gt; **Settings**

- **Duplicate** an existing Project by clicking the **three-dot menu** (appears on mouseover) &gt; **Duplicate**

- **Delete** an existing Project by clicking the **three-dot menu** (appears on mouseover) &gt; **Delete**

- **Select or create a new mapping schema** for an existing Project** **by clicking the **three-dot menu** (appears on mouseover) &gt; **Data Mapper**

- **Create a new Production** of an existing Project** **by clicking the **three-dot menu** (appears on mouseover) &gt; **Production**
